Aim

To interface stepper motor and control its direction.

Theory
Stepper motor rotates in steps
Direction depends on sequence
CW uses forward sequence
ACW uses reverse sequence
Delay controls speed
Used in robotics
Provides precise control
Simulator Used

EdSim51

🔹 Code – Clockwise (CW)
ORG 0000H
CW:
MOV P1, #08H
ACALL DELAY
MOV P1, #04H
ACALL DELAY
MOV P1, #02H
ACALL DELAY
MOV P1, #01H
ACALL DELAY
SJMP CW

DELAY:
MOV R6, #255
D1: MOV R7, #255
D2: DJNZ R7, D2
DJNZ R6, D1
RET
END
🔹 Code – Anticlockwise (ACW)
ORG 0000H
ACW:
MOV P1, #01H
ACALL DELAY
MOV P1, #02H
ACALL DELAY
MOV P1, #04H
ACALL DELAY
MOV P1, #08H
ACALL DELAY
SJMP ACW

DELAY:
MOV R6, #255
D1: MOV R7, #255
D2: DJNZ R7, D2
DJNZ R6, D1
RET
END
Observation
CW rotation observed using forward sequence
ACW rotation observed using reverse sequence
Speed controlled by delay
Smooth step movement
Conclusion

Thus, stepper motor direction control (CW and ACW) was successfully implemented.
